6:
Oh... I am so glad to see you safe...
Shakari!
8:
Hush... Have I not said before? It
would take a hurricane to topple an
old oak like me.
10:
*sniff* Yes... Of course...

How... went the reconnaissance?
13:
Poorly. Even now daemons threaten
to come knocking at our front door.
We must abandon this place.
16: But... we thought we'd be safe here...
19: ...I get the feelin' they aren't locals.
27:
We must seek shelter with the
Resistance. Only they can shield you
from uncertainty.
29:
I ask that you make this final
journey... To a safe haven.
32: But can they afford to take us all in?
33:
We are naught but women, children,
and withered elders. On the harsh
waves of war, we are dangerous
burdens. Is it not wiser to cast us
away?
35:
Do you think so little of Lilith? All my
words are in accordance with her
wishes.
38:
It is BECAUSE I love our lady that I
say this... For her sake, perhaps it
would be better if we were to meet
our ends here.
46:
Hey there! Are there beastfolk living
around here too?
50:
Hi! I'm Eric! Yeah, we've got some
beastfolk.
53:
But they aren't as hairy as your
friend.
63:
Whoa! Are you also beastfolk?
You're so fluffy! How do you float like
that?
71:
Ain't he cute? But just between you
and me, he's a cranky old man on
the inside. Think the stress of being a
champion is gettin' to him.
76:
A beast champion? Hehehe. That's
funny!
80:
Now, now, Eric. Why don't you leave
those weary travelers—
87:
You brought those monsters down
upon us... You invited death into our
midst!
91:
Stand down! They are currently
under my—
102:
It's coming! The Doomsday Lance is
here!
113:
Pandemonium has begun its
encroachment... No... Not here! Not
now!
116: Hehehe... Hello and how do you do?
121:
My name's Ilbis, and I've come to
introduce you all to my good friend...
destruction.
124:
Oh, but before the screaming
drowns everything out, why don't
you explain yourself... Stella?
127:
What are you doing here? You
should be with the King.
130: I don't know who you are.
133:
I knew it! She was in league with the
fiends all—
136: Was I talking to you, lady?
144:
You can't confuse me like this,
Stella... You KNOW I've got a few
screws loose.
148:
Maybe it'll be easier to think when
everyone's obliterated...
152:
All you self-absorbed infidels are
the same. So busy preening, you
never see death coming.
162: Oh, death's coming... But not for me!
